<seg id=1> Russian President on Russian Economy </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Moscow, January 8(xinhua)- Russia's primary achievement in 1997 was creating a fundamental condition for economic growing, Russian Prime Minister Chernomerdin said at the governmental meeting on Jan,8. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Itar-tass news, Russia's GDP last year was 1.2% up the 1996, industrial production up 3.2%, retail commodities up 3.9% and the yearly inflation rate was 11%, 50% down the 1996, citizens income up 2.5%, said Chernomerdin. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Chernomerdin also pointed out, quite a few domestic problems still existed last year, including dissatisfactory taxation, investment plans not fulfilled, reduced international trade surplus, government's monetary and financial measures not work effetively, etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> When talking about this year, Chernomerdin said that a new plan of economic structure reform and economic growth was being drafted and was to be discussed at the wider range government meeting on Feburary 26. </seg>
<seg id=6> In this plan, next year Russia's GDP is estimated to be up 2% and inflation rate is to be down to 5% to 8%. </seg>
</p>
